HEADWORD: Satchel
<hw>Satch"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>sachel</ets>, fr. L. <ets>saccellus</ets>, dim. of
<ets>saccus</ets>. See <er>Sack</er> a bag.]</ety> <def>A little sack or
bag for carrying papers, books, or small articles of wearing apparel; a
hand bag.</def> <altsp>[Spelled also <asp>sachel</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The whining schoolboy with his <qex>satchel</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sate</ent>⟦br⟧
